cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.CYBER, cs.AI 

This paper deals with simulations of infectious disease spread in social networks and the fairness implications of different treatment strategies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to simulate epidemic control, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the fairness implications of different treatment strategies, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper uses simulations to optimize the allocation of vaccines, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
